                  <scopecontent id="aspace_c83593d9c1359cc6936fe4e29966ebac">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>About the restoration of Percy Bysshe Shelley's tomb and the preparation of the adjoining grave for Edward John Trelawny's ashes, accompanied by 1 ALS from Rossetti to Trelawny, 12 November 1880, and a draft of a letter, unsigned, from Trelawny to Rossetti, 28 June 1879, on the same subject. Accompanied by drafts and translations of correspondence between Edward John Trelawny and John Trucchi, the Custodian of the English Cemetary at Rome about the repair of Shelley's tomb. Purchase, 1971,</p>
                  </scopecontent>
